# Plan Implementation

When executing an approved plan (or a plan attached to the conversation), follow this order **before** marking work complete.

## 1. Documentation (required)

Every plan that changes behavior, admin/organizer workflows, or player-facing UX must include doc work. Route by audience per `documentation.mdc` — do not skip because the plan omitted docs.

| Change type | Doc site | Typical path |
|-------------|----------|--------------|
| Event ops, scoring, internal APIs, RLS, Realtime | Admin | `docs/admins/docs/<kebab-case>.md` |
| Player/organizer how-to, dashboard UX | User | `docs/users/docs/<kebab-case>.md` |
| Both audiences | Split into two files | Never one mixed doc |

After editing markdown:

1. Update that site's `sidebars.ts` if the page is new or moved
2. Update `docs/intro.md` only when navigation or onboarding changes
3. Do **not** `git commit` inside `docs/admins/` or `docs/users/` unless the user explicitly asks

If no doc exists for the feature, extend the closest sibling (e.g. `event-management-admin.md` for admin event changes) rather than inventing a new file unless the plan specifies one.

**Admin doc content rules** (strict — see `documentation.mdc`):

- In-app workflows only; no `npm run`, `npx supabase`, or shell commands in published docs
- Never link to or mention `.cursor/` paths in admin or user markdown
- Migrations, deploy, env setup, and test commands belong in `.cursor/breakdowns/` and implementation replies for engineers, not in Docusaurus guides

**Published doc URLs** (for summary and Linear block — set in `.env` or replace when known):

| Site | Base |
|------|------|
| Admin | `ADMIN_DOCS_URL` or `https://<org>.github.io/clashpoint-admin-docs` |
| User | `USER_DOCS_URL` or `https://<org>.github.io/clashpoint-user-docs` |

Pattern: `{base}/{kebab-case-filename-without-md}` — e.g. `event-scoring-admin.md` → `…/event-scoring-admin`

## 2. Plan todo alignment

If the plan has a docs todo, complete it in the same pass as code — not as a follow-up.

If the plan has an E2E todo (or the feature matches `e2e-testing.mdc` "required" criteria), ship Playwright specs in the same pass — not as a follow-up.

When updating the plan file todos, mark the docs item done only after admin/user markdown reflects the shipped behavior. Mark E2E done only after specs exist or N/A is documented with reason.

## 3. Commit messages (suggest only)

Do **not** commit unless the user asks. At the end of plan implementation, provide **two** suggested commits when both app code and nested doc repos changed:

### A. ClashPoint monorepo

```
Summary: <imperative verb> <what changed> (<scope if helpful>)

<body — 1–3 sentences on why, not a file list>
```

Example summary lines: `Add fight join Server Action`, `Scope Realtime to fight channels`, `Fix leaderboard revalidation after score update`.

Match existing repo style: concise summary, body explains **why** and any deploy/ops action.

### B. Nested doc repos (only if markdown was edited)

Separate suggestion per repo touched (`docs/admins`, `docs/users`):

```
Summary: <same theme as app change, doc angle>

<body — what readers will find updated>
```

Remind the user: nested doc repos need their own commits with maintainer git identity when they choose to commit.

## 4. Breakdown file (required)

Every plan implementation, bug fix resolution, or feature rollout must create or update a breakdown in `.cursor/breakdowns/`. This folder is the **single source of truth** for what the user needs from each implementation (changelog, deploy steps, test commands, commit suggestions, Linear block).

**Breakdowns are internal.** Do not link to `.cursor/breakdowns/` from published Docusaurus docs. Supabase migrations, Vercel deploy, env vars, and manual test steps belong in breakdowns (and Linear deploy comments for engineers), not in admin/user guides.

### File location & naming

Save to `.cursor/breakdowns/` using this exact pattern:

```
YYYYMMDD-HHMM-<task-slug>-breakdown.md
```

| Part | Rule |
|------|------|
| `YYYYMMDD` | Local date when the breakdown is written |
| `HHMM` | Local 24-hour time (no colon), e.g. `1652` |
| `<task-slug>` | Short kebab-case label (e.g. `fight-join`, `leaderboard-realtime`, `event-scoring`) |
| Suffix | Always `-breakdown.md` |

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Create | On every completed plan, fix, or rollout |
| Update | Same topic later → append a dated changelog section to the latest breakdown for that slug; do not duplicate in the same session |

**Required content:**

- Title and date
- Summary (what changed and why)
- Bullet changelog of player-visible / organizer-visible changes
- Files touched (grouped: `app/`, `features/`, `supabase/`, `lib/`)
- Deploy steps if any (Supabase migration, Vercel, env vars)
- Manual test steps (URLs, flows — not Pest; suggest what to click/verify)
- E2E specs added/updated or N/A with reason; `npx playwright test` command when applicable
- Suggested ClashPoint commit (summary + body)
- Suggested doc commits if applicable
- Linear paste block (Title, Description, Comment/instructions, Documentation links)
- Published doc links when updated

## 5. Implementation summary (required)

End every plan implementation reply with a **changelog** the user can scan or paste elsewhere (mirror the breakdown changelog; link to the breakdown file when helpful):

```markdown
## <Short title — same theme as commit summary>

- <Player-visible or organizer-visible change>
- <Another concrete change>
- <Migration, env, or deploy note if any>
```

Use bullet points, not file lists. Cover behavior, organizer workflow, and player UX — skip refactors that change nothing observable.

## 6. Linear paste block (optional)

When the user tracks work in Linear, add a **copy-paste block** after the summary. Omit if they did not ask or the task is trivial.

```
Title: <same as summary title>

Description:
<2–5 sentences or bullets — what shipped and why>

Comment / instructions:
<Supabase migration, Vercel deploy, env vars, organizer follow-up, manual test notes>

Documentation:
<Only when docs were updated — one line per page>
Admin: {ADMIN_DOCS_URL}/<slug>
User: {USER_DOCS_URL}/<slug>
```

### Example (fight join flow)

```
Title: Add fight join Server Action and player guide

Description:
Players can join open fights from the event page. Join is validated server-side with Zod and RLS; the fight list revalidates after success. Realtime updates scoped to fight:{id}.

Comment / instructions:
Apply Supabase migration after deploy (`supabase db push` or run migration in dashboard). Set no new env vars. Test: open an event → Join Fight → confirm row in fights and leaderboard update.

Documentation:
Admin: https://<org>.github.io/clashpoint-admin-docs/fight-management-admin
User: https://<org>.github.io/clashpoint-user-docs/joining-a-fight
```

## 7. Response checklist

Before finishing, confirm in the reply:

- [ ] Breakdown file created or updated in `.cursor/breakdowns/`
- [ ] Admin doc updated (or N/A with reason)
- [ ] Admin docs: no CLI, shell blocks, or `.cursor/` references (per `documentation.mdc`)
- [ ] User doc updated (or N/A with reason)
- [ ] E2E specs added/updated (or N/A with reason per `e2e-testing.mdc`)
- [ ] Suggested ClashPoint commit summary + body
- [ ] Suggested doc commit(s) if applicable
- [ ] Implementation summary (title + bullets)
- [ ] Linear paste block (when useful or requested)
